U||Grundtvig, N.F.S.—Bjowulfs Drape. Copenhagen, 1820.
U||Heyne, M.—A translation in iambic measures. Paderborn, 1863.
U||Kemble, J.M.—The Anglo-Saxon Poems of Beowulf, the Traveller’s Song, and the Battle of Finnsburg. London, 1833. The second edition contains a prose translation of Beowulf.
U||Leo, H.—Ueber Beowulf. Halle, 1839. Translations of extracts.
U||[xii]
